---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Services — Mapache Softworks"
	description="Consulting, contracting, software development, developer education, and automation strategy from Mapache Softworks."
>
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container">
			<p class="eyebrow">Consulting and contracting</p>
			<h1>Software help for teams that want useful things shipped well.</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				Mapache Softworks can support focused engagements around product engineering, architecture, developer-facing experiences, workshops, and automation decisions.
			</p>
			<div class="hero-actions">
				<a class="button" href="mailto:hello@mapache-soft.com">hello@mapache-soft.com</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<div class="container grid">
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Software development</h3>
				<p>Hands-on implementation for web, mobile, macOS, APIs, integrations, release processes, and maintainable internal tooling.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Product and architecture</h3>
				<p>Decision support for scope, sequencing, technical direction, automation boundaries, and systems that should remain understandable.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Developer education</h3>
				<p>Workshops, onboarding material, reference implementations, documentation, and practical learning paths for engineering teams.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Developer relations</h3>
				<p>Technical content, product feedback loops, demos, talks, and adoption work for developer-facing products.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Automation strategy</h3>
				<p>Clear thinking around what to automate, what not to automate, and how to keep user trust intact when systems become more capable.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h3>Interim technical leadership</h3>
				<p>Short-term support for planning, hiring signals, delivery operations, and technical clarity during transitions or growth phases.</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<div class="container split">
			<div>
				<p class="eyebrow">Collaboration style</p>
				<h2>Best fit for small, thoughtful teams.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="panel">
				<ul class="list">
					<li>Discovery calls that turn vague problems into concrete options.</li>
					<li>Short advisory engagements for strategy, architecture, or product direction.</li>
					<li>Implementation sprints with clear scope and useful handover material.</li>
					<li>Remote-friendly work across Europe and beyond, with Vienna as a home base.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

